00:11:47.920 --> 00:11:50.990
a little model-- and like every
model, it's an approximation--

00:11:50.990 --> 00:11:52.990
a little model of how we
can understand thought.

00:11:52.990 --> 00:11:56.650
We can begin to think
of thought in two

00:11:56.650 --> 00:11:58.300
ways, two kinds of thought.

00:11:58.300 --> 00:12:04.600
Think of it like the waves
on the surface of a pond.

00:12:04.600 --> 00:12:08.380
So one kind of thought we
could call horizontal thoughts.

00:12:08.380 --> 00:12:10.930
A horizontal thought
means it's a thought that

00:12:10.930 --> 00:12:14.540
is generated by another
thought that was already there.

00:12:14.540 --> 00:12:16.060
In other words,
it's not original.

00:12:16.060 --> 00:12:18.050
It's not arising out of nowhere.

00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:21.880
It's a predictable thought that
was conditioned into your mind

00:12:21.880 --> 00:12:23.110
by an existing thought.

