drinking coffee to
get the deadline met,

00:47:44.010 --> 00:47:47.560
that's a practice
sometimes useful at 5:45.

00:47:47.560 --> 00:47:50.060
You can see you don't want to
live your whole life that way,

00:47:50.060 --> 00:47:53.600
but it's a great practice when
you need to meet a deadline.

00:47:53.600 --> 00:47:57.530
Right after 6 o'clock is,
not a very popular practice,

00:47:57.530 --> 00:47:59.420
but deliberately feeling pain.

00:47:59.420 --> 00:48:01.469
Stopping-- maybe
that's why sometimes

00:48:01.469 --> 00:48:02.510
why we go to a therapist.

00:48:02.510 --> 00:48:04.640
The therapist helps
you to feel pain

00:48:04.640 --> 00:48:06.230
you've been unwilling to feel.

00:48:06.230 --> 00:48:07.930
And under the right
circumstances,

00:48:07.930 --> 00:48:09.390
it's a great thing to do.

00:48:09.390 --> 00:48:12.080
That's a 6:15 practice.

00:48:12.080 --> 00:48:15.440
Making atonement-- very popular
in the 12-step movement--

00:48:15.440 --> 00:48:18.050
writing letters, I'm really
sorry I did this 30 years ago.

00:48:18.050 --> 00:48:19.340
I really feel bad about it.

00:48:19.340 --> 00:48:22.370
That's a repairing
practice at 7:30.

00:48:22.370 --> 00:48:24.890
Self-forgiveness--
going for a walk

00:48:24.890 --> 00:48:27.500
and really thinking about
that you're essentially

00:48:27.500 --> 00:48:30.770
a good person, getting in touch
with your essential goodness

00:48:30.770 --> 00:48:32.120
and forgiving yourself.

00:48:32.120 --> 00:48:34.850
That's an 8:45 practice.

00:48:34.850 --> 00:48:36.830
And in the last
segment, prayer, when

00:48:36.830 --> 00:48:40.220
you feel very separate from
something outside yourself,

00:48:40.220 --> 00:48:41.600
but you ask for help.

00:48:41.600 --> 00:48:43.910
That would be a practice
right after 9:00.

00:48:43.910 --> 00:48:46.040
Meditation would be
a practice that--

00:48:46.040 --> 00:48:49.040
or the beginning of meditation,
like Hinayana meditation.

00:48:49.040 --> 00:48:51.350
But as we get closer
to 12:00, there

00:48:51.350 --> 00:48:54.380
are practices designed to
just push you over the edge,

00:48:54.380 --> 00:48:57.620
like, for example, the Dzogchen
teachings in Tibetan Buddhism,

00:48:57.620 --> 00:49:01.010
or the self-enquiry
method of Ramana Maharshi.

00:49:01.010 --> 00:49:03.470
So that's the power of practice.

00:49:03.470 --> 00:49:06.650
And you can start to see now
the way that all this works is,

00:49:06.650 --> 00:49:09.560
if your intention in life
is brilliance-- people

00:49:09.560 --> 00:49:11.810
have a lot of-- there' are
a lot of ways to live life.

00:49:11.810 --> 00:49:13.880
You could live your
life for pleasure.

00:49:13.880 --> 00:49:16.040
You could live your
life for money.

00:49:16.040 --> 00:49:17.900
You could live
your life for fame.

00:49:17.900 --> 00:49:21.050
You could live your life
in all kinds of ways.

00:49:21.050 --> 00:49:25.730
But if you get just
a little taste--

00:49:25.730 --> 00:49:27.776
in German, they call it
[GERMAN],, which I think

00:49:27.776 --> 00:49:29.150
is a much better
word than taste.

00:49:29.150 --> 00:49:33.530
But if you just get this
little taste of the possibility

00:49:33.530 --> 00:49:36.160
of a life of contribution--

00:49:36.160 --> 00:49:39.380
and Google offers you this
incredibly generous opportunity

00:49:39.380 --> 00:49:41.240
with the 20% thing--

00:49:41.240 --> 00:49:45.800
a taste of what it's like to
live a life of contribution

00:49:45.800 --> 00:49:48.260
to the grandchildren
of your grandchildren,

00:49:48.260 --> 00:49:50.090
contributing to
the quality of life

00:49:50.090 --> 00:49:52.660
of people who are not yet born.

00:49:52.660 --> 00:49:54.660
When we get a little
taste of that,

00:49:54.660 --> 00:49:57.125
it becomes a positive addiction.

00:49:57.125 --> 00:49:58.250
You understand what I mean?

00:50:00.691 --> 00:50:02.690
If you drink alcohol,
it's a negative addiction.

00:50:02.690 --> 00:50:04.430
You drink more alcohol,
you smoke more cigarettes,

00:50:04.430 --> 00:50:06.096
going oh, I don't
want to be doing this.

00:50:06.096 --> 00:50:07.950
But contribution is
a positive addiction.

00:50:07.950 --> 00:50:10.620
The more you contribute
and serve other people,

00:50:10.620 --> 00:50:13.190
the better you feel about
yourself, the more energy

00:50:13.190 --> 00:50:15.599
you have, the more
money flows on its own

00:50:15.599 --> 00:50:17.390
without you having to
do anything about it.

00:50:17.390 --> 00:50:20.900
Contribution is a
positive addiction.

00:50:20.900 --> 00:50:24.050
The more we live a
life of contribution,

00:50:24.050 --> 00:50:27.440
the more we become
interested in fostering

00:50:27.440 --> 00:50:29.000
this quality of
brilliance, the more

00:50:29.000 --> 00:50:31.490
we become interested
in helping it along.

00:50:31.490 --> 00:50:34.940
And hopefully, what I've
shared with you today,

00:50:34.940 --> 00:50:38.960
is a very practical, repeatable,
verifiable way of doing that.

00:50:38.960 --> 00:50:40.160
Thanks for listening today.

